text: María José Corral Bouza (born 1991) is a Spanish volleyball player. She played at the 2017 Women's European Volleyball League, winning a bronze medal. She played for Dauphines Charleroi, Terville-Florange OC, CEP Poitiers Saint- Benoît, Quimper Volley 29, AJM/FC Porto, CSU Belor Galați, Paris Saint-Cloud. == References == == Other websites == * Athlete's biography, fivb.org Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Spanish sportspeople Category:Volleyball players
